g.text: What does it mean to be need-blind?

text.tspan: A policy in which a university won’t consider students’ financial
situation when deciding whether to admit them
It will apply to U.S. citizens, dual citizens and permanent residents,
The goal is to raise at least the majority of the estimated cost
To encourage students from disadvantaged backgrounds to feel
comfortable applying and to enable the university to admit the
most qualified students, regardless of family or personal finances
The university will seek a large lead gift in the amount of $75
million to $100 million to jumpstart the fundraising, followed by
